{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 03:05:30.228128", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and goal\\n- Validate end-to-end reachability in an enterprise OSPF multi-area network with DHCP relay at distribution, DNS and web services in 10.200.0.0/24, and hosts in 10.<core>.<dist>.0/24.\\n- Focus on detecting anomalies, localizing faulty devices, and identifying root causes.\\n\\nKey observations and tests\\n1) Host states (access layer)\\n- host_1_1_1_1 (10.1.1.x site):\\n  - No IP address on eth0; no default route.\\n    Evidence: get_host_net_config(host_1_1_1_1) shows no inet on eth0 and empty ip route.\\n  - Cannot reach DNS or server farm.\\n    Evidence: ping to 10.200.0.2 (dns_server) and 10.200.0.7 (load_balancer) -> “Network is unreachable”.\\n  - Web requests to web99.local/web0.local fail immediately (zeroed timings), consistent with no IP.\\n\\n- host_1_1_1_4 (same L2/L3 segment as above):\\n  - No IP address on eth0; no default route.\\n    Evidence: get_host_net_config(host_1_1_1_4) shows no inet on eth0 and empty ip route.\\n  - Cannot reach DNS or load balancer.\\n    Evidence: ping -> “Network is unreachable”.\\n  - Web requests to web99.local fail immediately.\\n\\n- host_2_1_1_1 (10.2.1.x site):\\n  - Has DHCP-acquired IP 10.2.1.14/24 and default route via 10.2.1.1.\\n    Evidence: get_host_net_config(host_2_1_1_1) shows inet 10.2.1.14/24, default via 10.2.1.1, “dynamic” lease.\\n  - Can reach DNS and load balancer and web servers.\\n    Evidence: ping dns_server and load_balancer successful; curl http://web99.local and http://web0.local complete with ~1s totals.\\n\\n2) Distribution layer\\n- router_dist_1_1 (gateway for 10.1.1.0/24):\\n  - OSPF configured in area 66 for both 10.1.1.0/24 and its uplink 172.16.0.6/31.\\n    Evidence: frr_show_running_config(router_dist_1_1): “network 10.1.1.0/24 area 66” and “network 172.16.0.6/31 area 66”.\\n  - No OSPF neighbors.\\n    Evidence: frr_exec show ip ospf neighbor returned header only (no neighbors).\\n  - Routing table contains only its directly connected networks; no routes to server farm or other areas.\\n    Evidence: frr_show_ip_route(router_dist_1_1) shows only connected 10.1.1.0/24 and 172.16.0.6/31.\\n\\n  - DHCP relay service is not running.\\n    Evidence: systemctl status isc-dhcp-relay on router_dist_1_1: “Active: inactive (dead)”.\\n\\n- router_dist_2_1 (gateway for 10.2.1.0/24):\\n  - OSPF configured in area 1 for 10.2.1.0/24 and link 172.16.0.14/31, with a full adjacency.\\n    Evidence: frr_show_running_config(router_dist_2_1) area 1; frr_exec show ip ospf neighbor shows Full with 172.16.0.14.\\n  - Has OSPF-learned routes to 10.200.0.0/24 and other site subnets.\\n    Evidence: frr_show_ip_route(router_dist_2_1) shows O>* routes to 10.200.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.14.\\n  - DHCP relay service is reported inactive, yet hosts have DHCP leases.\\n    Evidence: systemctl status isc-dhcp-relay on router_dist_2_1: inactive; host_2_1_1_1 has a “dynamic” IP and default route.\\n\\n3) Core and server access\\n- router_core_1:\\n  - OSPF is ABR with backbone area 0 and area 1; link to router_dist_1_1 is placed in area 1 on the core side (172.16.0.6/31 in area 1).\\n    Evidence: frr_show_running_config(router_core_1).\\n  - Has full adjacencies to other core routers and proper OSPF reachability to server farm 10.200.0.0/24.\\n    Evidence: show ip ospf neighbor (multiple Full); show ip route O>* 10.200.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.3.\\n- server_access_router:\\n  - OSPF has routes to all campus subnets via 172.16.0.22; server farm VLAN 10.200.0.0/24 is directly connected.\\n    Evidence: get_host_net_config(server_access_router) shows 10.200.0.1/24 on br0 and OSPF routes to 10.x/172.16.x via 172.16.0.22.\\n\\nAnomalies detected\\n- Access subnet 10.1.1.0/24 is non-functional for end hosts:\\n  - No DHCP address assignment observed on multiple hosts (host_1_1_1_1, host_1_1_1_4).\\n  - No IP or routes -> cannot reach DNS or server farm.\\n\\n- OSPF adjacency failure on router_dist_1_1:\\n  - Area mismatch across the uplink: router_dist_1_1 uses area 66 while router_core_1 expects area 1 for 172.16.0.6/31.\\n  - As a result, router_dist_1_1 forms no OSPF neighbors and does not learn routes to the rest of the network.\\n\\n- DHCP relay service state:\\n  - isc-dhcp-relay is inactive on both distribution routers according to systemctl.\\n  - Despite this, 10.2.1.0/24 hosts do obtain leases, while 10.1.1.0/24 hosts do not.\\n  - This discrepancy indicates either:\\n    - An alternative/embedded DHCP relay mechanism exists only for 10.2.1.0/24, or\\n    - The 10.2.1.0/24 host retained/renewed an existing lease while 10.1.1.0/24 cannot contact a DHCP server at all due to routing/relay issues.\\n  - Regardless, DHCP is definitively not functioning on 10.1.1.0/24.\\n\\nImpact assessment\\n- 10.1.1.0/24 user subnet is effectively isolated:\\n  - Hosts have no IP configuration and no path to DNS and web services.\\n  - Even if hosts obtained IPs, router_dist_1_1 currently lacks OSPF reachability to 10.200.0.0/24 due to area mismatch, so server access would still fail.\\n\\n- 10.2.1.0/24 user subnet is healthy:\\n  - Hosts have DHCP configuration, DNS resolution works, and HTTP access to web99.local and web0.local is successful.\\n  - End-to-end path through router_dist_2_1, core, and server_access_router is operating normally.\\n\\nLocalization of faulty devices\\n- Primary fault localized to router_dist_1_1:\\n  - OSPF area misconfiguration on uplink/subnet (set to area 66 instead of area 1 to match core).\\n  - DHCP relay not functioning (service inactive), correlating with hosts lacking DHCP configuration in 10.1.1.0/24.\\n\\n- No faults detected on router_dist_2_1, core routers, or server_access_router that would affect 10.2.1.0/24; those paths are confirmed working.\\n\\nRoot cause analysis\\n- Root cause 1: OSPF area mismatch between router_dist_1_1 and router_core_1 on link 172.16.0.6/31 prevents OSPF adjacency and route exchange. Router_dist_1_1 therefore has no routes to server and other networks.\\n  Evidence:\\n  - router_dist_1_1: network 172.16.0.6/31 area 66\\n  - router_core_1: network 172.16.0.6/31 area 1\\n  - No OSPF neighbors on router_dist_1_1; only connected routes present.\\n\\n- Root cause 2: DHCP relay not operating for 10.1.1.0/24 (and reported inactive on router_dist_1_1) so hosts on that subnet cannot obtain IP addresses.\\n  Evidence:\\n  - isc-dhcp-relay inactive on router_dist_1_1.\\n  - host_1_1_1_1 and host_1_1_1_4 have no IP/default route and cannot reach DNS or web services.\\n\\nHealthy/normal components\\n- router_dist_2_1 OSPF adjacencies and routing to 10.200.0.0/24 are correct; 10.2.1.0/24 host has functioning DHCP, DNS, and HTTP access.\\n- Core OSPF topology appears stable (multiple Full adjacencies on router_core_1; expected routes present).\\n- Server access segment 10.200.0.0/24 is reachable from 10.2.1.0/24 and serving HTTP via web99.local and web0.local.\\n\\nSummary\\n- Abnormal condition confirmed in the 10.1.1.0/24 domain: hosts have no DHCP leases and no routing to services.\\n- Fault localized to router_dist_1_1 with two misconfigurations:\\n  1) OSPF area mismatch (66 vs 1) causing routing isolation.\\n  2) DHCP relay not running, leading to no host IP configuration.\\n- The 10.2.1.0/24 domain operates normally end-to-end, validating the rest of the infrastructure., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='1b9fc635-e5f3-4f8a-b870-d527902e4aaa'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
